TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: call ABORT if the TBL_NM and SCHEMA_NM entered in the table RPS.TRBAT_PURG_RULE are not valid.
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
iif(isnull(Lkp_TABNAME), ABORT('The SCHEMA.TABLE_NAME passed in for PURG_RULE_ID:'||to_char(PURG_RULE_ID)||' is not valid.'))
--iif(isnull(Lkp_TABNAME), ABORT('The'|| SCHEMA_NM||'.'||TBL_NM||'passed in for PURG_RULE_ID:'||PURG_RULE_ID||' is not valid.'))
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: TABNAME_invalid_check

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Subtract (RTNTN_RANGE_NB +1) months from the current calendar month to drop the data 1 month older than the RTNTN_RANGE_NB
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_Month

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Subtract (RTNTN_RANGE_NB +1)*3 months from the current calendar month to drop the data 1 quarter older than the RTNTN_RANGE_NB.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_Quarter

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Subtract (RTNTN_RANGE_NB +1) years from the current calendar year to drop the data 1 year older than the RTNTN_RANGE_NB.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_Year

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: For timestamp case, this purge value is used to get the partition name from syscat.datapartitions table where this purge value falls between LOWVALUE and HIGHVALUE of the partition.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_PURG_VALUE_TS

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Get the Low range value. If purg_prd_cd is monthly: get the first day of the month (var_month). If Purg_PRD_CD is yearly:Get the year (var_Year). If Purg_Prd_cd is quarterly: Get the Quarter (var_Quarter).
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Get the Low range value. If purg_prd_cd is monthly: get the last day of the month (var_month). If Purg_PRD_CD is yearly:Get the year (var_Year). If Purg_Prd_cd is quarterly: Get the Quarter (var_Quarter).
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_PURG_RANGE_HIGH_VAL_TX

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Format Purge Low Range value (var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX). If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=1 (Date): Format Low Range value to date format YYYY-MM-DD. Note: date format YYYY-MM-DD is used to get the match from SYSCAT.DataPartitions table. If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=2 (Timestamp): Format Low Range value to date format YYYY-MM-DD|| 00:00:00.000000. Note: date format YYYY-MM-DD is used to get the match from SYSCAT.DataPartitions table. If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=3 (Quarter): Format Low Range value to quarter YYYYQ# format. If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=4 (Year): Format Low Range value to year format.
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: Decode (ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD , 1, TO_CHAR(var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX, 'YYYY-MM-DD') , 2, TO_CHAR (var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX, 'YYYY-MM-DD')||' 00:00:00.000000' ,3, TO_CHAR(var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX,'YYYY') ||'Q'|| TO_CHAR (var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX,'Q') , TO_CHAR(var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX,'YYYY') )
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX_Format

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Format Purge High Range value (var_PURG_RANGE_HIGH_VAL_TX). If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=1 (Date): Format high Range value to date format. If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=2 (Timestamp): Format high Range value to YYYY-MM-DD|| 23:59:59.999999. If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=3 (Quarter): Format high Range value to quarter YYYYQ# format. If ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=4 (Year): Format high Range value to year format.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_PURG_RANGE_HIGH_VAL_TX_Format

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: For partition drop request, get the partition name from SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS based on table name, schema name, low value and high value.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: var_PRTN_NM

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: If TBL_STRTR_CD =1 (Partition), set the value to New. If TBL_STRTR_CD =2 (Non Partition), set the value to Pending.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: PURG_ACTN_CD

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Set the value to 1 (Partition) for partition drop and to 2 (REORG) for delete statement.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: PURG_ACTN_TYP_CD

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: For timestamp case (ACTN_COL_FRMT_CD=2) and partition table (TBL_STRTR_CD =1), get LOWVALUE from lookup LKP_DATAPARTITIONS_TS_LOWVALUE based on schema name, table name and partition name.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: out_PURG_RANGE_LOW_VAL_TX

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: For timestamp case (Partition), get HIGHVALUE from lookup LKP_DATAPARTITIONS_TS_HIGHVALUE based on schema name, table name and partition name.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: out_PURG_RANGE_HIGH_VAL_TX

TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_DATAPARTITIONS_TS

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup Sql Override
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS.DATAPARTITIONNAME as DATAPARTITIONNAME , LTRIM(RTRIM(SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS.TABSCHEMA)) as TABSCHEMA , LTRIM(RTRIM(SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS.TABNAME)) as TABNAME , REPLACE(LTRIM(RTRIM(SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS.LOWVALUE)), '''','') as LOWVALUE , REPLACE(LTRIM(RTRIM(SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS.HIGHVALUE)), '''', '') as HIGHVALUE FROM SYSCAT.DATAPARTITIONS -- the REPLACE is for removing the single quotes from the data

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup policy on multiple match
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: Use Any Value

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Lookup condition
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: TABSCHEMA = in_SCHEMA_NM AND TABNAME = in_TBL_NM AND LOWVALUE <= in_PURG_VALUE_TS AND HIGHVALUE >= in_PURG_VALUE_TS

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Null ordering
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: Null Is Highest Value
